    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move shared GPU tile op lowering code into `src/backend/common/op`.\n- Keep CUDA and ROCm files focused on target matching, registration, and platform-specific strategy hooks.\n- This refactor is motivated by the high structural similarity between several GPU tile ops across the CUDA and ROCm backends.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Added common lowerers for `fill`, `transpose`, `cumsum`, `atomic_reduce`, `reduce`, and `finalize_reducer`.\n- Replaced duplicated CUDA/ROCm implementations with thin backend registration files.\n- Preserved backend-specific behavior for AllReduce barrier selection, warp size handling, and fp16/bf16 NaN reduce support.\n- Left `copy`, `atomic_add`, and `gemm` unchanged because their CUDA and ROCm implementations diverge substantially.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `./format.sh`\n- `cmake --build build --target tilelang_objs -j$(nproc)`\n- ROCm `-fsyntax-only` checks for `fill`, `transpose`, `cumsum`, `atomic_reduce`, `reduce`, and `finalize_reducer`\n\n## Notes\n\n- The local CMake cache has `USE_ROCM=OFF`, so ROCm validation was limited to syntax-only checks with the current TileLang include set.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Unified implementations of core tensor operations across CUDA and ROCm GPU backends, including atomic operations, cumulative sum, reduction, transpose, and fill operations.\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
